# 5. 残りの日を大切に

KAITO: So, Minori, you and Haruka are ready to switch to the credit-based course?
Minori: Yup!
Minori: I wasn't really sure at first... But after giving it a lot of thought, I made a decision that I feel happy with!
Luka: Hehe. That's wonderful to hear.
Len: When you and I talked, you said schoolwork might be a challenge... Does this mean you know what you're gonna do about that?
Minori: Oh, um... Not exactly since I won't know how a lot of things go until I actually give it a try...
Minori: But I've just gotta do the best I can!
Minori: Also, Airi, Shizuku, I can always ask you two if I have any questions since you've both been in it for so long now.
Airi: Hehe. Ask us whenever you like♪
Shizuku: Yes, we'll be more than happy to help if we can.
Haruka: The four of us will probably be studying together during our time off, which I'm actually sort of looking forward to...
Minori: Oh, me too!!!
Minori: Wait, then! We can stream that! What do you think?! We can call it something like “Let's Study with MORE MORE JUMP!”
Airi: I'd rather not. It'd be way too hard to focus.
MEIKO: Hehe. In any case, it's nice to hear that you're all looking forward to being in the credit-based course.
Rin: Yeah! By the way, when do you plan on making the switch...?
Minori: Really soon! I asked my teacher about it and was told that there are two opportunities per year to switch. Once in spring and once in the fall.
Haruka: Which works out really well since we're all about to move up a year.
Miku: I see... Oh, that means you get to be regular students until you begin your second year!
Minori: Yeah, but it's still happening pretty soon. That's why I want to treasure the time I have left.
Minori: I don't wanna find myself looking back after making the switch and saying, “No, I should've done that back then!”
KAITO: That's understandable...
Rin: Okay, you two! That means you really gotta have fun during the time you have left as regular high schoolers!
Minori: Thanks, we will!
Minori: Okay, I'm gonna get going now!!!
Minori's Mother: Bye. Have fun at school.
Minori's Brother: Bye... Hmm... Is it just me, or did she sound more excited than usual?
Minori's Mother: She did say something about trying to enjoy the time she has left as a regular high school student.
Minori's Brother: Uh, okay...? I guess that makes sense...?
Minori: Wow, this breeze feels so nice! And my usual walk to school feels so different when I look at it in a new way!
Minori: Oh! This flower is finally blooming!
Minori: (Hehe. I was wondering when it would after seeing it budding just the other day...)
Minori: I have a really good feeling about today.
Kohane: Good morning, Minori. You seem really happy today. Even more than usual.
Minori: Oh! Morning, you two!
Minori: You gotta see this! I found this flower the other day, and now it's finally blooming!
Shiho: Oh, really? It's growing out of the asphalt too. It must be pretty hardy.
Kohane: It's so pretty! I hope the crows don't decide to pick it apart or anything.
Minori: No, that'd be awful! And way too soon! It just started blooming today!
Minori: But I'm really glad we got to see it today. There's actually another one budding just up ahead!
Minori: Once it blooms, we can see it...
Minori: (Oh, right...)
Minori: (I get to see these flowers with Shiho and Kohane because we go to school at the same time.)
Minori: (But after I go credit-based...)
Miya Girls Students: Hey, did you guys see that sweets special yesterday?! The cafe they showed is apparently really close by.
Miya Girls Students: I heard an old alumnus is coming to visit our club today! I hope they're not too hard on us this time...
Miya Girls Students: No, I totally forgot about that assignment! Can you show me what you did?! Please, I'll never ask for anything again...!
Minori: (Everyone chatting with each other while we all head to school... I won't get to see that as much moving forward...)
Minori: (I never really thought of things this way before. It was all just “normal”...)
Minori: Right...
Shiho: Minori...?
Minori: (The little things in life that happen every day. I guess I took it all for granted until now.)
Minori: (Then, I've gotta do my best to see everything else I've been taking for granted.)
Minori: (That way, after I do go credit-based, I'll be able to look back fondly on all the fun stuff I did!)
Minori: Minori Hanasato is still a regular high schooler! And she's gonna make the final sprint to reach the next chapter of her life! “Part 2: Full-Time Idol!”
Shiho: What are you talking about...?
???: <...>
Miku: <Minori sounds really excited.>
KAITO: <Yes, she does. Still...>
KAITO: <I wasn't expecting you to suggest seeing what her school's like, Len.>
Luka: <Me neither... What made you want to do this all of a sudden?>
Len: <It wasn't as sudden as you think. I began wondering after Airi told us her story the other day.>
Len: <I wasn't able to give her any useful advice then since I didn't really know anything about what it's like to go to school or be a student. It wasn't a good feeling...>
Len: <So, I wanna learn more about their school.>
Rin: <That makes sense...>
Len: <They ended up figuring everything out all on their own before I could do anything...>
Len: <But school means a lot to them, so I wanna know what it's like to be a student.>
MEIKO: <Right...>
MEIKO: <They always enjoy talking about things that happen at school and their friends there, but we've never actually seen that for ourselves...>
MEIKO: <Learning about their school life could very well help us give them better advice if anything else comes up in the future.>
Miku: <True...>
Miku: <Then, let's go see what Minori is like as a student and what her school is like!>
Luka: <Hehe. We'll need to make sure she doesn't see us.>
KAITO: <I'm not sure how I feel about us sneaking around like this... But I wouldn't want to ruin what precious little time she has left with her friends.>
MEIKO: <Me neither. I wouldn't want to say something and make Minori concern herself with us.>
Rin: <So, everyone, shush! We gotta keep our voices down!>
Len: <You're the one I'm most worried about, Rin...>
